    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "That's a good start. Can you expand on the \"marketplace of ideas\" part? I want to dive deeper into the idea that any state intervention—even if it's meant to stop misinformation or hate speech—is fundamentally illegitimate because it's impossible for a government to be a neutral arbiter. How would a philosopher like John Stuart Mill or a libertarian theorist frame that specific point?",
